			</p>
		</div>
		<div id="general-guidelines">
			<h3>I: General Guidelines </h3>
      <p> For <a href="/apply">applications</a> to help beta test services, we reserve the right to accept or deny any applicants that is not against the <a href="https://atproducts.xyz/titleiiandvii">Title II and VII policy</a> in accordance of the <a href="https://www.archives.gov/milestone-documents/civil-rights-act">The Civil Rights Act of 1964</a> regarding volunteers. 
      <br><br> All beta testers are considered volunteers, meaning they are not considered employees as no payment will be made to the volunteers (beta testers). Beta testers may unenroll by contact <a href="mailto:support@atproducts.xyz">support@atproducts.xyz</a>. Once unenrolled, one final email may be sent out to confirm your unenrollment, then we will no longer contact you regarding beta testing services.
      <br><br> Beta Testers may be removed if they break the main website's <a href="https://atproducts.xyz/terms">Terms of Service</a> or <a href="https://atproducts.xyz/discord">Discord Rules</a>. </p>
		</div>
		<div id="acceptance">
			<h3> II: Acceptance </h3>
			<p> Upon submitting your <a href="/apply">application</a>, You signify your agreement to the following guidelines. In the circumstance that You violate any section of the guidelines, We reserve the right to revoke Your privileges and ability to beta test as mentioned prior. <br>
			<br> At our sole discretion, we reserve the right to modify or replace these guidelines at any time. If a revision has a sufficient effect on You, we will make efforts to provide at least a 30-day notice before any new Terms take effect. Just so you know, a sufficient revision is determined at Our sole discretion.
			</p>
		</div>
